  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: abbreviation, description, entity, human, location, numeric.\n\nImportant classification guidelines:\n- \"entity\" should be used for questions asking about specific things, objects, or concepts (e.g., \"What keeps clouds in the air?\" is asking about a specific thing/concept that keeps clouds aloft, so it should be classified as \"entity\")\n- \"description\" should be used for questions asking for explanations of how or why something works, or asking for definitions or descriptions of processes\n- \"human\" should be used for questions about specific people or groups of people\n- \"location\" should be used for questions about places or geographical locations\n- \"numeric\" should be used for questions asking for numbers, quantities, dates, or measurements\n- \"abbreviation\" should be used for questions asking what an acronym or abbreviation stands for\n\nPay careful attention to what the question is fundamentally asking for. If a question uses the word \"what\" but is asking for a specific entity or thing (rather than a description or explanation), classify it as \"entity\" rather than \"description\"."
